DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

# output the text of the problem

$p = random(100,150,10);
$c = random(100,200,10);
$n = random(200,300,10);
$co1 = $p+$c;
$co2 = $p*$n-2000;


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

The same company produces skis, too. Fixed costs are ${DOLLAR}2000, and
the cost of producing each pair of skis is $DOLLAR$c. The selling price is 
$DOLLAR$co1 (per pair). How many pairs should be sold to make a profit of
$DOLLAR$co2?

$BR

Answer:   \{ans_rule(30)\}

EOT

$ans1 = $n;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

